I knew this would come.<br>
<br>
Quin and Aauminki, i think you have to differntiate a little more.<br>
<br>
I, as a Wizard, want to do mainyl damage, and i do that nicely. In the Tier 4 planes (PoFIres) for example a lot of mobs are immune to run speed changes.<br>
If they are not, it is often hard (not impossible, but hard) to get a snare on them. I ended up one day with wasting 400 mana just because i had to cast snare 4, 5 times untill it sticked.<br>
<br>
Of course this changes if in your group is a tashing chanter present.<br>
Now let me assure you something: Since PoP my groups have not whiped because i have not snared and we got a 'runner'. I just kill those mobs, when they turn and try to run, this is much more efficient (in my very personal opinion and for my play-style) than to snare them.<br>
I prefer to invest mana in a Lure to be sure to kill them or in a standard nuke than into a resistant biatch snare.<br>
Aside that, even IF you shoul get an add because of a runner... , please that here is not 1999, my groups are able to handle an add, and i would love sometimes that 'auto-pull' feature. (As i said, has not happened yet, because the mobs were only able to move 2 feet from me, untill i my nuke send them to the Nirwana.)<br>
<br>
This is as well true for dungeon-like zones like CoD, where i find myself more often these days, to help to level some alts.<br>
<br>
Second: Stuns.<br>
Stuns are nice to have to, but NOT to save the chanter any more, lol. They are much more usefull in those incidents when a Mob tries to gate and the only exp zone in PoP i am aware of, where this happends is BoT. Aside the fact that BoT is suck exp and i don't group there often, it is the ONLY place where i use Telekin.<br>
<br>
With my now 308 AA (grats me, yay<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) and 6400ish HP buffed i can tank quite well in those places, often better than low AA meatshields. Same applies for chanters with there arcane rune. AT least the chanters i group with have absolutly no problem to get their debuffs to stick and have not died every because i did not stun an ele-plane Mob. Oh please. Again, we are not in 1999 anymore.<br>
Then again, i would have only ONE spell that is able to stun high tier exp mobs and that is Telekin. If it gets resisted i have to wait anyway 163478 years untill it refreshes.<br>
Nope, i see no reason to mem Telekin (in my very personal play-style) other than in BoT.<br>
<br>
If you can tell me any reason why i should use that spell on Xegony (lol, why should i? I prefer to SoS her for allmost the same mana), please do so - it could be interesting.<br>
<br>
HoH and theirlikes... That are the places where i can really tank now efficiently (IF i have to), especially if a Mob is snared. Heck, the Mobs die within 20-40 seconds (manaproblem is no issue there for me since you can use a horse there) and i end up chain casting SoS, why should i even mem a snare or a stun?<br>
<br>
Groups love me, because i speed up their kills massively and am not afraid to nuke. I do this by nuking, and not by stunning or snaring. Who needs a snare, if the Mob is dead?<br>
<br>
Ya, i know this will differ so much from other's playstyles. Ya, i know there are Wiz out there who prefer to chain stun (which is not even possible anymore in the higher tier planes of PoP). But this is not MY playstyle. <br>
I just blow things up and am not afraid of getting then and when aggro. I can very well stand a beating. And groups love me for blowing things into oblivion.<br>
<br>
Finally, this is my adviuce for you, who have often troubles finding a group:<br>
Blow things up, show them that YOU speed up their exp rate massively. YOU are the killer in that group and not the monk or rogue or ranger.<br>
And allways remember: only a dead mob is a good mob. <br>
<br>
And a dead mob can't run or hurt the chanter or cleric.<br>
<br>
