<br>
Telekin is a 9 second stun.  Your average slow mob will probably land about 5-6 hits in that time.  You have time to toss off concussions afterwards, and with SCS3 I never had a problem using Telekin frequently and avoiding agro with a single concussion after a telekin.  Using it somewhat frequently, you can cut a mob's total damage output by 1/6 to 1/5, which helps a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>lot</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> with shaman and druid healers.<br>
<br>
This goes into the whole &quot;a wizard does not just nuke&quot; ethic.  Nuking is what a wizard does best, but it's not the thing he has to be doing.  Knowing the situations where it'd be more advantegous to emphasize your other skills is what makes you a good wizard.  (shaman + necro + rogue + mage + warrior + wizard = awesome group.  But not many people try to think different. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
