<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>There are circumstances where it's better to nuke stuff down. You seem to still think that the only use for snare is to keep mobs from running away.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Is there any other use? You still did not tell me, Enlighten me please.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>As far as losing stats on the orb.... having 100 less mana for 15 seconds really doesn't break my balls too much, since really mana and effects are the only stats that tend to matter after a while.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
155 mana/hp and some FT. And no, i don't melee still.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>1) Crowd control. A snared mob doesn't move fast.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
True, and? Does it matter?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>A smart group is capable of killing things on one side of a room while you hold the mobs on the other.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I yet have to find a zone where my group needed to 'hold some mobs' at the other end of a room, while killing some other stuff. Did not happen to me in PoP. Aside that = One resisted snare in those completly theoretical situations and you have in ANY case some REAL issues then <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>2) Train management. Works best in outdoor zones, although there are plenty of indoor zones where if you have enough space (get in the way-back machine- halls in akheva were just wide enough to work this), you can snare mobs off of a train, turning a 10 mob stab at exodus into some sweet xp and one hell of a fight.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
You talk about AE groups or so? Never felt the urge to do AE again since PoP, nor have i ever experienced someone pulling for a standard group the way you described it, nor would i personally ever do it that way. I prefer to med and let others pull singles or doubles or triples.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I do have others, but I prefer to keep some of my tricks to myself. I fully expect you to poo-poo and say &quot;oh, that's too hard, I can't do full damage during that, wah wah wah&quot;, which is fine, I already stated that there are situations where maybe tons of damage isn't the thing your group needs most, and I know there are quite a few places in PoP, even in the elemental planes, where you can use both tactics. Not every place, so none of this &quot;snare-immune&quot; crap people like to toss off as if it were the rule instead of the exception.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Sure bro, everyone is entitled to his opinion, but i truely believe that you are constructing obscure theoretical situations here that just don't happen and are not realistical in PoP these days. (And that's where i do exp.)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Did you read the part I said about druid or shaman healers? The right tools for the right situations. Yes, you might not have a purpose to Telekin when you've got an overabundance of healing, but you also don't always have to have a cleric healer.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Hm... i do this when grouping with druids or shamans, too (as main healers).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>SITUATIONAL. I will force this through your head with a brick if need be, but once again everyone in the game does not have 300 aa, play at right below the end game, and have the strongest people to group with.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Sure i know this, this is why i added my last phrase and soon (in your next quotes) you are going to bash me for that, heh and accusing me of bragging. Make up your mind, Claud, finally.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>As well, that's 18 seconds if you want to use Telekin again. It's far from wasted time, after you've tossed off one concussion you're pretty much free to nuke, or, if you're a big tanking fan, don't even bother and land a SoS while he's stunned. It's far from a &quot;wasted&quot; 18 seconds, the &quot;cast a fucking draught&quot; comment was supposed to be thickly sarcastic.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
It's a waste of mana and wasted time, in my very own opinion, and in my playstyle i am much better off spending the 300 mana on an AT which does 4 times the damage. (And the lifepsan of those Mobs does not exceed much more than 18 seconds anyway and everything is better than a resisted Telekin...)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>There weren't many times I ever had to say &quot;LFG&quot;. Or ask a friend if they had openings in a group. Sometimes I had to fight for it if I wanted some time to quad. I never went looking for groups, the people who grouped with me in the past came looking for me. I don't need this &quot;maybe they'll reinvite you&quot; shit, I never had to worry about being reinvited. I could safely assume I would be. Sounds like I'm stroking my cock here, but I'm not.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Too much info... heh, do with your cock what you want to do...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Now, you can't always have a chanter. I'd rather spend the time I would have spent hunting one down killing mobs, and doing so in a way that's not the standard, accepted way of play. As far as what's &quot;more impressive&quot;... any idiot can nuke. Nuking is by far the easiest thing a wizard does. This is not a big secret to most people, only idiots still go &quot;oooh, aaah&quot; at 6k crits anymore. But nuking is not the only skill wizards get, and there are situations where one is better than the other. And there are very few situations I've found, even while doing CC, where I couldn't put out at least moderate damge. Not many wizards I know who CC almost as well as a chanter, and KEI's readily available in the nexus.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Yup, yup, it's your view of this issue, my view is different:<br>
 Dead Mobs &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; resisted snare, root, telekin. That's my opinion. Most groups have already a form of CCer avaiable (aside the Wizards Ghetto-CCing).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>SITUATIONAL USAGE. If you'd like to sit there and stroke it and say &quot;well groups only want damage&quot;, that's fine, I can sit hear and know that's bullshit, I can say &quot;people that grouped with me wanted Claud for his damage, and the fact that he could bail us out of a jam if we got into it&quot;.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Ah bro, again i don't strike something, like you do, heh. It's your opinion, thats ok.<br>
Groups invite me, because they know i dish out a TON of damage, and if something goes wrong i even can offtank for them AND do damage and i DO that. That's my form of crowd controlling.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>So... now, you're talking about a very slim sub-section of the game as if it was indicative of the entire game? You've got to stop hauling out the &quot;Well, in plane of fire we do THIS&quot;, and &quot;in plane of fire, we do THAT&quot;, I have my elemental flags to, no one's sitting here thinking you're more uber because you have a lot of aa and flags, stop dragging that out wherever you can as it's obvious you're trying to use it to make it seem like you're the great uber wise player. (Else, you wouldn't say it nearly as often.) AA is nothing special, AA = time. Flags are nothing special, I've known quite a few people in the top guilds of the game who were absolutely clueless<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Heh and now you are bashing me, because i say: My 'thing' might not be suitable for every other Wizard or it might not be every Wizard's preference to do it this way, especially if they are NOT 65 and have NOT the essential defensive AAs?<br>
(I especially refer to your first quote where you jumped on me for saying this.)<br>
<br>
Claud you know what... you should wonder, why SoE did not continue after SoL (safe Telekin) to give us that many Stuns like they used to do pre 60... We are in 99% a DAMAGE dealing class.<br>
And i try to avoid everything that takes away from my DPS. That's why groups invite me. Might be different for you, Claud, but it is that way for me.<br>
